commit.message:
Merge pull request #8 from DatekWireless/master

* Change use of #attr into #attr_reader and #attr_accessor...

Merge pull request #1 from sunaku/master

add synchronize() method like Ruby's Mutex API
* Change use of #attr into #attr_reader and #attr_accessor to keep up with Ruby API changes and avoid noisy warnings.

add Lockfile#synchronize() method; like Mutex API

because passing a block to Lockfile() or
Lockfile.new() does not yield the advertised
Mutex#synchronize()-like behavior in Ruby 1.9
fire up refresher thread when lock called without a block - code cleanup

fixing warnings under ruby 1.9

Signed-off-by: ahoward <ara.t.howard@gmail.com>
more house keeping and gemspec cleanup
clean up vim fold marks in lib
